# Dev Tooling MCP

**Trigger:** Datei/Klasse/Methode verstehen, `find_file`, `read_signatures_only`, `scaffold_angular`, `scaffold_dotnet`, Scaffolding, Build, Test, `ng build`, `ng test`, `dotnet build`, `dotnet test`.

**Router:** [dev-tooling-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-tooling-mcp/SKILL.md)

## Kanon-Skills (Parameter + JSON)

| Situation | Tool | Skill laden |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| Lesen/Suchen unter `/project/...` | dev-filesystem-mcp | [dev-filesystem-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-filesystem-mcp/SKILL.md) |
| Angular `ng generate` | `scaffold_angular_component` / `scaffold_angular_service` | [dev-angular-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-angular-mcp/SKILL.md) |
| Angular **Build** | `build_angular_project` (dev-angular-mcp) | [dev-angular-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-angular-mcp/SKILL.md) |
| Angular **Test** | `test_angular_project` (dev-angular-mcp) | [dev-angular-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-angular-mcp/SKILL.md) |
| `dotnet new` / Ordnerstruktur | `scaffold_dotnet_project` / `create_directory_structure` | [dev-dotnet-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-dotnet-mcp/SKILL.md) |
| .NET **Build** | `build_dotnet_solution` (dev-dotnet-mcp) | [dev-dotnet-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-dotnet-mcp/SKILL.md) |
| .NET **Test** | `test_dotnet_solution` (dev-dotnet-mcp) | [dev-dotnet-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-dotnet-mcp/SKILL.md) |
| Review, Index, Komplexität | **codebase-analyzer** | [codebase-analyzer/SKILL.md](../skills/codebase-analyzer/SKILL.md) |

## VERBOTEN — Hard Stop

**`ng build` / `ng test` / `dotnet build` / `dotnet test` niemals als Shell-Kommando** wenn MCPs verfügbar.

| Falsch | Richtig |
|--------|---------|
| Shell: `ng build` | `build_angular_project` via dev-angular-mcp |
| Shell: `ng test` | `test_angular_project` via dev-angular-mcp |
| Shell: `dotnet build` | `build_dotnet_solution` via dev-dotnet-mcp |
| Shell: `dotnet test` | `test_dotnet_solution` via dev-dotnet-mcp |
| `build-log-filter` für Build/Test | MCPs filtern intern — `errors[]` direkt auswerten |

**Wenn MCP nicht erreichbar:** `BLOCKER: [dev-angular-mcp | dev-dotnet-mcp] nicht erreichbar` melden — **kein** stiller Shell-Fallback ohne explizite Nutzerfreigabe.

**Pflicht:** Tool-Schema aus `mcps/<server>/tools/*.json` lesen, dann aufrufen — keine geratenen Keys.
